<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 31 at 3:53PM CDT  by NWS Chicago</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of north central Ford
and northwestern Iroquois Counties through 415 PM CDT...
At 353 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Cullom, or 11 miles northeast of Chatsworth, moving northeast at 55
mph.
HAZARD...Nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Cabery, Kempton and Stelle.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for central,
northeastern and east central Illinois.</instruction>
